cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a method of identifying fraudulent honey using machine learning augmented microscopy. This involves using computer vision techniques to analyze images of honey samples and identify any adulteration or mislabelling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms to analyze the images suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of microscopy to capture the images suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
